WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.926 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.926 --> 00:00:02.778 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:02.778 --> 00:00:06.030 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.030 --> 00:00:10.740 align:middle line:84%
>> "Thinking Allowed,"
conversations on the leading

00:00:10.740 --> 00:00:14.690 align:middle line:84%
edge of knowledge and discovery
with psychologist Jeffrey

00:00:14.690 --> 00:00:15.490 align:middle line:90%
Mishlove.

00:00:15.490 --> 00:00:32.400 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:33.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello and welcome.

00:00:33.340 --> 00:00:35.000 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jeffrey Mishlove.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:38.310 align:middle line:84%
Today we're going to
explore the wellspring

00:00:38.310 --> 00:00:40.440 align:middle line:90%
of women's spirituality.

00:00:40.440 --> 00:00:45.000 align:middle line:84%
I'm pleased to be with Dr. Jean
Shinoda Bolen, Jungian analyst,

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:47.190 align:middle line:84%
member of the
Department of Psychiatry

00:00:47.190 --> 00:00:50.550 align:middle line:84%
at the University of California
Medical School in San

00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:54.120 align:middle line:84%
Francisco, and author of
a number of classic books,

00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:58.470 align:middle line:84%
including "Goddesses in
Everywoman," "Gods in Everyman"

00:00:58.470 --> 00:01:02.310 align:middle line:84%
"The Tao of Psychology,"
"Crossing to Avalon,"

00:01:02.310 --> 00:01:05.850 align:middle line:84%
"Close to the Bone,"
and "The Ring of Power."

00:01:05.850 --> 00:01:06.960 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Jean.

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:07.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:01:07.840 --> 00:01:09.520 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a pleasure
to be with you.

00:01:09.520 --> 00:01:13.890 align:middle line:84%
You know, when I think
of esoteric culture,

00:01:13.890 --> 00:01:18.420 align:middle line:84%
the mystery traditions around
the world, authentic mysticism,

00:01:18.420 --> 00:01:21.990 align:middle line:84%
over and over again
it actually strikes me

00:01:21.990 --> 00:01:27.540 align:middle line:84%
that all mystical traditions
are about feminine spirituality,

00:01:27.540 --> 00:01:30.750 align:middle line:84%
about preserving something
that has been lost

00:01:30.750 --> 00:01:33.000 align:middle line:90%
in the patriarchal culture.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:36.850 align:middle line:10%
>> I would agree that it's
about the experience itself.

00:01:36.850 --> 00:01:41.650 align:middle line:10%
So it's not about having a
book or a transcendent god

00:01:41.650 --> 00:01:45.870 align:middle line:10%
speaking from above or
giving the message to someone

00:01:45.870 --> 00:01:47.400 align:middle line:10%
who passes it on.

00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:49.170 align:middle line:10%
It's non-hierarchical.

00:01:49.170 --> 00:01:51.230 align:middle line:10%
And it isn't about words.

00:01:51.230 --> 00:01:54.300 align:middle line:10%
So consequently, anything
that is a mystery

00:01:54.300 --> 00:01:56.250 align:middle line:10%
is a mystical experience.

00:01:56.250 --> 00:02:00.110 align:middle line:84%
It is an experience that you
know intuitively in your heart,

00:02:00.110 --> 00:02:01.530 align:middle line:90%
in your soul.

00:02:01.530 --> 00:02:04.420 align:middle line:90%
And you have it.

00:02:04.420 --> 00:02:12.300 align:middle line:84%
You can't take it and
make somebody else believe

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:16.450 align:middle line:84%
in it, not that you're
even inclined to do so.

00:02:16.450 --> 00:02:19.890 align:middle line:84%
So in that way, it's
a more feminine model

00:02:19.890 --> 00:02:25.710 align:middle line:84%
of being receptive to the
mystical, spiritual experience,

00:02:25.710 --> 00:02:30.800 align:middle line:84%
feeling it in your body soul,
and then having an experience

00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:33.600 align:middle line:90%
that changes you.

00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:39.240 align:middle line:84%
And it's an experience
that I felt that,

00:02:39.240 --> 00:02:43.140 align:middle line:84%
because it's so
personal, that you

00:02:43.140 --> 00:02:46.560 align:middle line:84%
have to have some
way of describing it

00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:48.640 align:middle line:90%
through your own life.

00:02:48.640 --> 00:02:52.500 align:middle line:84%
So I wrote "Crossing to Avalon"
as a story of my own midlife

00:02:52.500 --> 00:02:53.370 align:middle line:90%
pilgrimage.

00:02:53.370 --> 00:02:56.250 align:middle line:84%
But it was far more
than a personal story.

00:02:56.250 --> 00:02:58.110 align:middle line:84%
It was really the
vehicle in order

00:02:58.110 --> 00:03:02.970 align:middle line:84%
to describe what it is that I
had discovered along the way

00:03:02.970 --> 00:03:06.480 align:middle line:84%
and put into words
of women's often

00:03:06.480 --> 00:03:08.850 align:middle line:90%
mystical spiritual experiences.

00:03:08.850 --> 00:03:14.880 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're in a
traditional society where

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:19.530 align:middle line:84%
religion owns all the words,
all the spiritual words

00:03:19.530 --> 00:03:22.380 align:middle line:84%
like "sacramental,"
like "grace,"

00:03:22.380 --> 00:03:27.420 align:middle line:84%
then you can have an experience
that is enormously sacramental,

00:03:27.420 --> 00:03:31.500 align:middle line:84%
but it isn't in any kind
of official experience.

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:33.540 align:middle line:84%
And what happens if
you have an experience

00:03:33.540 --> 00:03:35.400 align:middle line:84%
and you don't have
words for it is it

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:38.730 align:middle line:84%
goes back into the
psyche, forgotten.

00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:41.550 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things, if
you go out on a pilgrimage,

00:03:41.550 --> 00:03:45.330 align:middle line:84%
is that as you go
towards this place,

00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:49.290 align:middle line:84%
you also go in and start
to think about and remember

00:03:49.290 --> 00:03:51.330 align:middle line:90%
experiences you've had.

00:03:51.330 --> 00:03:54.480 align:middle line:84%
So I was invited to
go on a pilgrimage

00:03:54.480 --> 00:04:00.750 align:middle line:84%
to visit my own spiritual
sources, is what it began as.

00:04:00.750 --> 00:04:04.060 align:middle line:84%
>> That's an interesting
term, "sources."

00:04:04.060 --> 00:04:05.610 align:middle line:90%
>> It's true.

00:04:05.610 --> 00:04:08.280 align:middle line:84%
The whole idea turned out
to be very interesting,

00:04:08.280 --> 00:04:10.480 align:middle line:90%
because I didn't realize--

00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:15.600 align:middle line:84%
since I was at the
start of my 49th year

00:04:15.600 --> 00:04:22.670 align:middle line:84%
and also my profession
as a Jungian an analyst,

00:04:22.670 --> 00:04:25.400 align:middle line:84%
I'm not in my body
very much in my work.

00:04:25.400 --> 00:04:26.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm in my intuition.

00:04:26.650 --> 00:04:30.090 align:middle line:84%
I might say I'm in my
feelings and in my mind,

00:04:30.090 --> 00:04:35.790 align:middle line:84%
but that I actually might pick
up information, especially

00:04:35.790 --> 00:04:39.090 align:middle line:84%
spiritual experience,
through my body

00:04:39.090 --> 00:04:43.110 align:middle line:84%
and then remember that lots
of other previous experiences

00:04:43.110 --> 00:04:45.270 align:middle line:84%
fit that description
also is what I

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:47.850 align:middle line:90%
did with "Crossing to Avalon."

00:04:47.850 --> 00:04:53.250 align:middle line:84%
Now, I didn't
realize that people

00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:57.060 align:middle line:84%
had been going on pilgrimages
for thousands of years

00:04:57.060 --> 00:04:59.730 align:middle line:90%
to quicken their divinity.

00:04:59.730 --> 00:05:04.540 align:middle line:84%
And once I got a sense of
those particular words,

00:05:04.540 --> 00:05:09.800 align:middle line:84%
it really struck me that I know
what those words are about.

00:05:09.800 --> 00:05:10.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Quicken the divinity.

00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:11.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Quicken the divinity.

00:05:11.850 --> 00:05:16.840 align:middle line:84%
Because as a pregnant woman,
I knew that I was pregnant.

00:05:16.840 --> 00:05:18.510 align:middle line:90%
Test said I was.

00:05:18.510 --> 00:05:20.190 align:middle line:90%
I was tired.

00:05:20.190 --> 00:05:22.320 align:middle line:90%
Body was changing.

00:05:22.320 --> 00:05:23.730 align:middle line:84%
And what a difference
it was when

00:05:23.730 --> 00:05:29.420 align:middle line:84%
I felt movement of new
life, my baby moving in me.

00:05:29.420 --> 00:05:33.150 align:middle line:84%
That is how we use the
word "quicken," you see.

00:05:33.150 --> 00:05:36.620 align:middle line:84%
So what does it mean if you use
it about quicken the divinity?

00:05:36.620 --> 00:05:39.170 align:middle line:84%
Why would you go to
places of pilgrimage

00:05:39.170 --> 00:05:40.310 align:middle line:90%
to quicken the divinity?

00:05:40.310 --> 00:05:42.080 align:middle line:90%
What might that mean?

00:05:42.080 --> 00:05:45.020 align:middle line:90%
That was the mystery.

00:05:45.020 --> 00:05:48.980 align:middle line:84%
So then I go to
Chartres Cathedral,

00:05:48.980 --> 00:05:51.770 align:middle line:84%
and I go through the
Cathedral the first time

00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:56.480 align:middle line:84%
like a sightseer, art
history student, appreciator

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:57.720 align:middle line:90%
of all the beauty around me.

00:05:57.720 --> 00:05:58.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Much to see.

00:05:58.550 --> 00:06:01.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Much to see.

00:06:01.250 --> 00:06:07.490 align:middle line:84%
And then, because I
remember that there was a--

00:06:07.490 --> 00:06:10.730 align:middle line:84%
this was a Black Madonna site
before it was a Christian site,

00:06:10.730 --> 00:06:14.810 align:middle line:84%
and that there was a well
somewhere at this site.

00:06:14.810 --> 00:06:17.930 align:middle line:84%
And I gathered that it was in
the crypt of this cathedral.

00:06:17.930 --> 00:06:21.680 align:middle line:84%
So I had an opportunity to go
on a sort of unofficial tour

00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:26.600 align:middle line:84%
down into the crypt with a
guide who didn't speak English.

00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:30.770 align:middle line:84%
So here again, we're making
a descent, basically.

00:06:30.770 --> 00:06:32.140 align:middle line:90%
Lighting is dim.

00:06:32.140 --> 00:06:34.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm in an unusual
place, an unusual land.

00:06:34.730 --> 00:06:36.980 align:middle line:84%
Somebody is talking to
me in a foreign language.

00:06:36.980 --> 00:06:38.188 align:middle line:90%
>> Under this huge cathedral.

00:06:38.188 --> 00:06:40.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Under this huge
cathedral, right.

00:06:40.760 --> 00:06:43.040 align:middle line:90%
And something is shifting in me.

00:06:43.040 --> 00:06:46.460 align:middle line:84%
And I think it has to do with
moving out of the left brain,

00:06:46.460 --> 00:06:50.660 align:middle line:84%
out of that mind that is
educated and therefore has

00:06:50.660 --> 00:06:54.200 align:middle line:84%
this view of things, into
the perceptive mind that

00:06:54.200 --> 00:06:56.730 align:middle line:90%
has her own experience.

00:06:56.730 --> 00:06:59.660 align:middle line:84%
So I do this, and then I
come up to the Cathedral.

00:06:59.660 --> 00:07:02.210 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it's
like inner and outer

00:07:02.210 --> 00:07:05.660 align:middle line:84%
often happen together, that
when I'm deeply moved inside,

00:07:05.660 --> 00:07:09.590 align:middle line:84%
some synchronicity on the
outside happens to enhance it.

00:07:09.590 --> 00:07:12.140 align:middle line:84%
So this time when I come
up in the Cathedral,

00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:14.710 align:middle line:84%
it's like the organist
begins to play.

00:07:14.710 --> 00:07:17.210 align:middle line:84%
So I have background
music to this.

00:07:17.210 --> 00:07:19.100 align:middle line:84%
And now I don't
have to sight see

00:07:19.100 --> 00:07:21.590 align:middle line:90%
because I've seen that place.

00:07:21.590 --> 00:07:25.070 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm feeling is
that there's energy here

00:07:25.070 --> 00:07:26.940 align:middle line:90%
that I'm picking up in my body.

00:07:26.940 --> 00:07:30.330 align:middle line:84%
And now I'm just
moving to the church,

00:07:30.330 --> 00:07:32.750 align:middle line:84%
to where the energy
is the greatest.

00:07:32.750 --> 00:07:35.510 align:middle line:10%
And I realized that I
have in my body what

00:07:35.510 --> 00:07:39.710 align:middle line:10%
could be like a tuning
fork to the energy.

00:07:39.710 --> 00:07:45.710 align:middle line:10%
And where the transepts
cross the nave,

00:07:45.710 --> 00:07:47.930 align:middle line:10%
that was where the
energy in front of-- it

00:07:47.930 --> 00:07:49.040 align:middle line:10%
was in front of the altar.

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:50.930 align:middle line:84%
That was the energy was
the greatest for me.

00:07:50.930 --> 00:07:52.490 align:middle line:84%
And as I stood
there and just was

00:07:52.490 --> 00:07:54.770 align:middle line:84%
receptive to what was
coming into my mind,

00:07:54.770 --> 00:07:57.950 align:middle line:84%
I realized that if I were
as large as this Cathedral,

00:07:57.950 --> 00:08:00.560 align:middle line:84%
like this, where
the labyrinth was--

00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:04.490 align:middle line:84%
is would be where my
uterus or womb is.

00:08:04.490 --> 00:08:08.390 align:middle line:84%
And isn't this-- and this whole
sense of this feminine space

00:08:08.390 --> 00:08:12.650 align:middle line:84%
that I was in began
to make me realize

00:08:12.650 --> 00:08:15.330 align:middle line:84%
that this might be something
about the quickening

00:08:15.330 --> 00:08:16.130 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:08:16.130 --> 00:08:19.020 align:middle line:84%
That is, you feel
something in your body.

00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:23.120 align:middle line:84%
And it is involved with
the energy of the place.

00:08:23.120 --> 00:08:26.870 align:middle line:84%
So might we truly all
be spiritual beings

00:08:26.870 --> 00:08:29.630 align:middle line:90%
on this human path, our souls?

00:08:29.630 --> 00:08:34.010 align:middle line:84%
Might we be moved to go on
pilgrimage, to go to places

00:08:34.010 --> 00:08:35.960 align:middle line:90%
where they said divinity lived?

00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:39.780 align:middle line:84%
But what happens there is that
you become aware that it's

00:08:39.780 --> 00:08:41.330 align:middle line:90%
been in you all the time.

00:08:41.330 --> 00:08:44.179 align:middle line:84%
>> If I understand the
chronology correctly,

00:08:44.179 --> 00:08:48.590 align:middle line:84%
by the time you had gone on this
pilgrimage, you were already,

00:08:48.590 --> 00:08:50.570 align:middle line:84%
I dare say, a
world-famous author.

00:08:50.570 --> 00:08:54.000 align:middle line:84%
Your book "Goddesses in
Everywoman" was a best-seller.

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:55.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Right, it was.

00:08:55.280 --> 00:08:59.480 align:middle line:84%
>> And you now here in
the heart of a cathedral

00:08:59.480 --> 00:09:03.320 align:middle line:84%
and in the underground
grotto, the cave,

00:09:03.320 --> 00:09:06.710 align:middle line:84%
ancient cave and wellspring
under that cathedral,

00:09:06.710 --> 00:09:09.890 align:middle line:84%
something was
awakened within you,

00:09:09.890 --> 00:09:14.120 align:middle line:84%
perhaps something about which
you had been writing for years,

00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:17.850 align:middle line:84%
but now you were
experiencing in a new way.

00:09:17.850 --> 00:09:20.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, I certainly was
experiencing something in a new

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:22.262 align:middle line:84%
way, but it wasn't what
I was writing about.

00:09:22.262 --> 00:09:24.470 align:middle line:84%
Because when I was writing
"Goddesses in Everywoman,"

00:09:24.470 --> 00:09:26.390 align:middle line:84%
I was writing about
the archetypes,

00:09:26.390 --> 00:09:29.610 align:middle line:84%
the psychological
archetypes in women.

00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:33.110 align:middle line:84%
What was interesting is
it became a beginning text

00:09:33.110 --> 00:09:36.668 align:middle line:84%
for a grassroots women's
spirituality movement.

00:09:36.668 --> 00:09:38.960 align:middle line:84%
And it's because when you
get into the archetypal level

00:09:38.960 --> 00:09:41.690 align:middle line:84%
of the psyche and when
you touch into symbols,

00:09:41.690 --> 00:09:45.200 align:middle line:84%
you are entering the
mystery of the deepening

00:09:45.200 --> 00:09:47.090 align:middle line:90%
of your experience.

00:09:47.090 --> 00:09:50.780 align:middle line:84%
So a symbol becomes
imbued with meaning,

00:09:50.780 --> 00:09:54.230 align:middle line:84%
and therefore it becomes a
spiritual kind of experience.

00:09:54.230 --> 00:09:56.250 align:middle line:90%
So I knew that was happening.

00:09:56.250 --> 00:09:58.190 align:middle line:10%
But when I went
on this pilgrimage

00:09:58.190 --> 00:10:01.760 align:middle line:10%
and was affected by
the energy of the place

00:10:01.760 --> 00:10:06.650 align:middle line:10%
and began to remember
from an embodied place,

00:10:06.650 --> 00:10:09.350 align:middle line:10%
I started to have a
different concept about how

00:10:09.350 --> 00:10:13.100 align:middle line:10%
women's spirituality is a
spirituality in which you are

00:10:13.100 --> 00:10:16.880 align:middle line:10%
bringing back what could
be called the Goddess

00:10:16.880 --> 00:10:21.230 align:middle line:10%
or a spirituality
that is of the body,

00:10:21.230 --> 00:10:24.720 align:middle line:10%
in which sacred
experience is felt

00:10:24.720 --> 00:10:26.990 align:middle line:10%
in relationship to the Earth.

00:10:26.990 --> 00:10:28.500 align:middle line:10%
And this is true
of lot of people,

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:30.810 align:middle line:10%
that they have their
most sacramental moments

00:10:30.810 --> 00:10:35.610 align:middle line:10%
sometimes out under the stars,
out in nature, men and women.

00:10:35.610 --> 00:10:38.130 align:middle line:10%
But then, what it
also reminded me

00:10:38.130 --> 00:10:41.850 align:middle line:10%
was of the experiences
of bearing a child

00:10:41.850 --> 00:10:47.490 align:middle line:10%
and how that was one of the
deepest spiritual experiences,

00:10:47.490 --> 00:10:49.695 align:middle line:10%
and yet because it
wasn't defined as such.

00:10:49.695 --> 00:10:52.290 align:middle line:90%


00:10:52.290 --> 00:10:54.730 align:middle line:90%
Women have had babies forever.

00:10:54.730 --> 00:10:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And I was a doctor
who delivered babies

00:10:56.820 --> 00:10:58.650 align:middle line:84%
before I had this
experience of having

00:10:58.650 --> 00:11:01.680 align:middle line:90%
one, which was very different.

00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:07.590 align:middle line:84%
But I had thought of myself as
an exception until this point.

00:11:07.590 --> 00:11:09.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Jean, we'll be
taking a brief break.

00:11:09.450 --> 00:11:10.950 align:middle line:84%
We'll be back in
just a few moments.

