00:11:15.531 --> 00:11:20.330 align:middle line:90%


00:11:20.330 --> 00:11:21.960 align:middle line:84%
Welcome back to
"Thinking Allowed."

00:11:21.960 --> 00:11:23.990 align:middle line:90%
I'm your host, Jeffrey Mishlove.

00:11:23.990 --> 00:11:26.180 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about
the wellspring

00:11:26.180 --> 00:11:29.430 align:middle line:84%
of women's spirituality
with Dr. Jean Shinoda

00:11:29.430 --> 00:11:32.750 align:middle line:84%
Bolen, author of
"Crossing to Avalon"

00:11:32.750 --> 00:11:36.120 align:middle line:90%
and "Goddesses in Everywoman."

00:11:36.120 --> 00:11:39.680 align:middle line:84%
If I understand correctly
what you're saying,

00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:42.320 align:middle line:84%
Jean, that you came
to the realization

00:11:42.320 --> 00:11:46.100 align:middle line:84%
that the goddess is more than
an archetype, but an energy.

00:11:46.100 --> 00:11:48.920 align:middle line:10%
And even more than an
energy, the goddess

00:11:48.920 --> 00:11:53.120 align:middle line:10%
is the living experience
of billions of women.

00:11:53.120 --> 00:11:59.150 align:middle line:10%
>> And men too, because I
began to realize that in my own

00:11:59.150 --> 00:12:02.660 align:middle line:10%
spiritual journey, I did know
what transcendent divinity was

00:12:02.660 --> 00:12:07.340 align:middle line:10%
like because my
childhood was Christian.

00:12:07.340 --> 00:12:13.310 align:middle line:84%
And there really was a
true sense of transcendence

00:12:13.310 --> 00:12:14.630 align:middle line:90%
and connection.

00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:17.540 align:middle line:10%
>> You were a devout Christian
as a child, I gather.

00:12:17.540 --> 00:12:20.410 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, no.

00:12:20.410 --> 00:12:22.970 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, at last you wrote about
it as if there were moments.

00:12:22.970 --> 00:12:24.740 align:middle line:84%
>> No, but there was
definite moments.

00:12:24.740 --> 00:12:27.380 align:middle line:84%
My life really changed
when I was an adolescent

00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:30.440 align:middle line:84%
and went to a very
Christian summer camp

00:12:30.440 --> 00:12:38.060 align:middle line:84%
and had a life-changing interior
experience that sent me out

00:12:38.060 --> 00:12:42.350 align:middle line:84%
to be a doctor because I felt
such a sense of gratitude

00:12:42.350 --> 00:12:44.930 align:middle line:84%
for everything I
had, and that one way

00:12:44.930 --> 00:12:49.010 align:middle line:84%
I could show it or repay it,
which I never could really,

00:12:49.010 --> 00:12:50.340 align:middle line:90%
was to serve other people.

00:12:50.340 --> 00:12:54.560 align:middle line:84%
And so I did have this
adolescent idealistic notion

00:12:54.560 --> 00:12:56.897 align:middle line:84%
that came out of the spiritual
experience of service.

00:12:56.897 --> 00:12:57.980 align:middle line:90%
>> In a Christian country.

00:12:57.980 --> 00:13:00.130 align:middle line:90%
>> In a very Christian context.

00:13:00.130 --> 00:13:06.380 align:middle line:84%
And I followed it, and
it has meant a lot to me.

00:13:06.380 --> 00:13:08.780 align:middle line:84%
But now I was adding this
whole other dimension.

00:13:08.780 --> 00:13:10.320 align:middle line:90%
And it wasn't just--

00:13:10.320 --> 00:13:13.510 align:middle line:84%
it isn't just saying that
we'll change the name from god

00:13:13.510 --> 00:13:14.310 align:middle line:90%
to goddess.

00:13:14.310 --> 00:13:16.760 align:middle line:84%
It was a whole
different experience,

00:13:16.760 --> 00:13:19.160 align:middle line:84%
because there is a
god of spirituality

00:13:19.160 --> 00:13:24.590 align:middle line:84%
or a feminine mystery or
an embodied sacred that

00:13:24.590 --> 00:13:31.490 align:middle line:84%
is about the divine that
is in the material world.

00:13:31.490 --> 00:13:34.740 align:middle line:84%
And it's about the beauty
that we experience there,

00:13:34.740 --> 00:13:38.030 align:middle line:84%
the sense of being held
in an energy field,

00:13:38.030 --> 00:13:43.670 align:middle line:84%
but through and within
something that is material.

00:13:43.670 --> 00:13:46.400 align:middle line:84%
And it is a mystery,
in a sense that mystery

00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:50.390 align:middle line:84%
comes from the
word "mystes," that

00:13:50.390 --> 00:13:53.690 align:middle line:84%
was the name of the
people who were initiated

00:13:53.690 --> 00:13:56.780 align:middle line:90%
into the Eleusinian mysteries.

00:13:56.780 --> 00:13:59.000 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, yeah,
there was something

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:02.090 align:middle line:84%
about learning
directly that there's

00:14:02.090 --> 00:14:07.280 align:middle line:84%
this realm of the sacred
that is of goddess or is

00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:10.220 align:middle line:84%
of women's spirituality
or essentially

00:14:10.220 --> 00:14:12.950 align:middle line:84%
is one of the mystical
ways of things.

00:14:12.950 --> 00:14:16.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, if I may be concrete,
and to follow up on what you

00:14:16.490 --> 00:14:18.980 align:middle line:84%
said earlier, a
woman gives birth.

00:14:18.980 --> 00:14:20.390 align:middle line:90%
A woman nurses.

00:14:20.390 --> 00:14:21.680 align:middle line:90%
A woman menstruates.

00:14:21.680 --> 00:14:25.070 align:middle line:84%
A woman is penetrated
in the sexual act.

00:14:25.070 --> 00:14:29.970 align:middle line:84%
All of these things are unique
to the physical experience

00:14:29.970 --> 00:14:30.770 align:middle line:90%
of women.

00:14:30.770 --> 00:14:34.220 align:middle line:84%
And as you write
about them, I come

00:14:34.220 --> 00:14:37.220 align:middle line:84%
to see that they and the
emotions that accompany them

00:14:37.220 --> 00:14:39.800 align:middle line:90%
are awesomely profound.

00:14:39.800 --> 00:14:40.760 align:middle line:90%
>> They can be.

00:14:40.760 --> 00:14:43.640 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that
really is significant

00:14:43.640 --> 00:14:47.510 align:middle line:84%
is that they're all very
physical experiences that

00:14:47.510 --> 00:14:53.990 align:middle line:84%
can be oppressive, can be
terrible under terrible

00:14:53.990 --> 00:14:57.140 align:middle line:90%
circumstances, and they can be.

00:14:57.140 --> 00:15:00.950 align:middle line:84%
But they have a possibility
of being extraordinarily

00:15:00.950 --> 00:15:04.370 align:middle line:84%
sacred under another
set of circumstances

00:15:04.370 --> 00:15:11.270 align:middle line:84%
in which the soul of the
woman is in the experience

00:15:11.270 --> 00:15:14.520 align:middle line:84%
and is picking up not
just on the physical side

00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:18.590 align:middle line:84%
but on the whole sacred
experience of being

00:15:18.590 --> 00:15:23.540 align:middle line:84%
like the goddess
who is giving birth,

00:15:23.540 --> 00:15:30.030 align:middle line:84%
is nursing, is making love, is
holding, is being the mother.

00:15:30.030 --> 00:15:34.130 align:middle line:84%
>> The epitome of
nurturing, I think.

00:15:34.130 --> 00:15:38.060 align:middle line:84%
>> The epitome of
being human about it,

00:15:38.060 --> 00:15:40.220 align:middle line:84%
because there is
something about how,

00:15:40.220 --> 00:15:43.880 align:middle line:84%
when you want to be comforted,
it does matter that the person

00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:47.030 align:middle line:84%
is in a body comforting
you, for example.

00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:50.900 align:middle line:84%
And what if, besides the
body that is comforting you,

00:15:50.900 --> 00:15:54.570 align:middle line:84%
it is within an energy field
as well that is of the goddess?

00:15:54.570 --> 00:15:56.780 align:middle line:84%
Now, that's something
of what I was describing

00:15:56.780 --> 00:15:58.810 align:middle line:90%
in "Crossing to Avalon."

00:15:58.810 --> 00:16:03.770 align:middle line:84%
And the title comes from a
book called "Mists of Avalon."

00:16:03.770 --> 00:16:06.110 align:middle line:84%
I was inspired by
"Mists of Avalon,"

00:16:06.110 --> 00:16:10.160 align:middle line:84%
the idea that you can cross
the mists from Glastonbury

00:16:10.160 --> 00:16:11.270 align:middle line:90%
to Avalon.

00:16:11.270 --> 00:16:15.110 align:middle line:84%
Glastonbury is a real place
in England that I went to

00:16:15.110 --> 00:16:17.310 align:middle line:84%
and described in
"Crossing to Avalon."

00:16:17.310 --> 00:16:21.210 align:middle line:84%
But it's also the mythical site
where you could call a barge

00:16:21.210 --> 00:16:24.630 align:middle line:84%
and go through the mist
to another reality, which

00:16:24.630 --> 00:16:27.750 align:middle line:84%
was Avalon, where
Glastonbury and Avalon are

00:16:27.750 --> 00:16:33.000 align:middle line:84%
two aspects of the same
but different realities.

00:16:33.000 --> 00:16:36.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Avalon being
the mythical realm,

00:16:36.660 --> 00:16:39.720 align:middle line:90%
the Kairotic timeless realm.

00:16:39.720 --> 00:16:41.700 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:16:41.700 --> 00:16:45.780 align:middle line:84%
And there is that Kairos
versus Chronos, linear time,

00:16:45.780 --> 00:16:49.590 align:middle line:84%
logical, rational
world, mental world,

00:16:49.590 --> 00:16:55.200 align:middle line:84%
and the devalued feminine,
Kairos, timeless.

00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:56.020 align:middle line:90%
>> Eternal.

00:16:56.020 --> 00:16:57.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Eternal.

00:16:57.210 --> 00:16:59.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Odd that we should
devalue eternity.

00:16:59.610 --> 00:17:01.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:17:01.860 --> 00:17:05.940 align:middle line:84%
>> But to me, this is a key to
the idea of women's mysteries.

00:17:05.940 --> 00:17:07.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Or-- well, it's
human mystery.

00:17:07.670 --> 00:17:10.250 align:middle line:84%
It's when the two
worlds overlap,

00:17:10.250 --> 00:17:12.839 align:middle line:84%
where the invisible world
and the visible world

00:17:12.839 --> 00:17:15.569 align:middle line:84%
somehow become one, or
the archetypal world

00:17:15.569 --> 00:17:18.180 align:middle line:84%
and the ordinary
world cross over.

00:17:18.180 --> 00:17:20.369 align:middle line:84%
And you're in this
liminal threshold

00:17:20.369 --> 00:17:25.300 align:middle line:84%
place, where you are in this
world, human being, woman--

00:17:25.300 --> 00:17:29.940 align:middle line:84%
say, giving birth-- and
you are at that moment

00:17:29.940 --> 00:17:34.150 align:middle line:84%
aware that there's this other
energy, reality, archetype,

00:17:34.150 --> 00:17:37.695 align:middle line:84%
goddess, whatever
you want to name it,

00:17:37.695 --> 00:17:40.950 align:middle line:84%
of which you are
participating in that moment,

00:17:40.950 --> 00:17:45.510 align:middle line:84%
and that you are in
that moment tuning in,

00:17:45.510 --> 00:17:50.280 align:middle line:84%
touching in to a
embodied mystery.

00:17:50.280 --> 00:17:52.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And there is a sense when
you refer to the goddess,

00:17:52.890 --> 00:17:54.110 align:middle line:90%
if I'm correct--

00:17:54.110 --> 00:17:56.700 align:middle line:84%
and I think I've experienced
this once or twice--

00:17:56.700 --> 00:17:58.680 align:middle line:90%
a sense of being embraced.

00:17:58.680 --> 00:18:00.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:18:00.360 --> 00:18:06.140 align:middle line:84%
Or being-- there's something
about awe and wonder.

00:18:06.140 --> 00:18:09.930 align:middle line:84%
The word numinous describes
all of our experiences

00:18:09.930 --> 00:18:12.780 align:middle line:84%
where we are touched
by something.

00:18:12.780 --> 00:18:16.060 align:middle line:84%
And the word "ineffable" is
usually attached to them,

00:18:16.060 --> 00:18:17.820 align:middle line:84%
so we aren't doing
very well with words.

00:18:17.820 --> 00:18:18.990 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:18:18.990 --> 00:18:22.980 align:middle line:84%
>> But there is that place where
something that is material,

00:18:22.980 --> 00:18:26.970 align:middle line:84%
that is, not invisible,
spiritual like patriarchal

00:18:26.970 --> 00:18:30.690 align:middle line:84%
monotheism says everything
that matters usually is,

00:18:30.690 --> 00:18:32.470 align:middle line:90%
and we are deeply moved by it.

00:18:32.470 --> 00:18:35.130 align:middle line:84%
And it could be a
very male experience

00:18:35.130 --> 00:18:37.710 align:middle line:84%
of being an astronaut looking
at Earth from outer space

00:18:37.710 --> 00:18:39.510 align:middle line:84%
and seeing the
beauty of the planet

00:18:39.510 --> 00:18:42.780 align:middle line:84%
and realizing in the
heart, this is mother,

00:18:42.780 --> 00:18:44.670 align:middle line:84%
and that we are all
indigenous here.

00:18:44.670 --> 00:18:47.310 align:middle line:90%
Something changes us.

00:18:47.310 --> 00:18:48.930 align:middle line:90%
It's the same experience.

00:18:48.930 --> 00:18:51.330 align:middle line:84%
But we shift from just
being in the left brain

00:18:51.330 --> 00:18:53.910 align:middle line:84%
to some liminal
space between the two

00:18:53.910 --> 00:18:57.850 align:middle line:84%
and picking up on
another dimension.

00:18:57.850 --> 00:19:05.370 align:middle line:84%
And if people learn to trust
their own spiritual experiences

00:19:05.370 --> 00:19:08.940 align:middle line:84%
and not look to other people
to define whether it qualifies

00:19:08.940 --> 00:19:12.000 align:middle line:84%
or not, then the
world is remarkably

00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:15.620 align:middle line:90%
filled with sacred moments.

00:19:15.620 --> 00:19:18.900 align:middle line:84%
>> In your pilgrimage that
you wrote about in "Crossing

00:19:18.900 --> 00:19:22.380 align:middle line:84%
to Avalon," there were many
moments when you had intimate

00:19:22.380 --> 00:19:25.810 align:middle line:84%
conversations with other women
who were accompanying you.

00:19:25.810 --> 00:19:29.940 align:middle line:84%
And you also recall memories
of times in your life

00:19:29.940 --> 00:19:33.120 align:middle line:84%
where you felt, if I
understand it correctly,

00:19:33.120 --> 00:19:35.010 align:middle line:84%
that in the presence
of another woman

00:19:35.010 --> 00:19:38.040 align:middle line:84%
is the possibility,
for both men and women,

00:19:38.040 --> 00:19:43.590 align:middle line:84%
of a greater kind of intimacy,
a being heard, being understood

00:19:43.590 --> 00:19:49.110 align:middle line:84%
more than in either male-female
or male-male relationships,

00:19:49.110 --> 00:19:51.210 align:middle line:90%
typically.

00:19:51.210 --> 00:19:55.920 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I think that there is
something about when you are

00:19:55.920 --> 00:19:57.350 align:middle line:10%
with your opposites.

00:19:57.350 --> 00:20:01.350 align:middle line:90%
There is an element of union.

00:20:01.350 --> 00:20:05.190 align:middle line:10%
When you're with-- when it's two
women, that there's something

00:20:05.190 --> 00:20:08.610 align:middle line:10%
about reunion, because it's
back to a mother-child dyad

00:20:08.610 --> 00:20:13.890 align:middle line:10%
that is different than the
meeting with one's opposite.

00:20:13.890 --> 00:20:19.110 align:middle line:84%
And so they're different
experiences is all I'm saying,

00:20:19.110 --> 00:20:23.460 align:middle line:84%
is that there is
a quality that is

00:20:23.460 --> 00:20:28.350 align:middle line:84%
different between union and
reunion in the energy field.

00:20:28.350 --> 00:20:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And there's something about how
you validate and find yourself

00:20:32.190 --> 00:20:36.750 align:middle line:84%
if you are open to speak of what
you truly experience and you

00:20:36.750 --> 00:20:41.310 align:middle line:84%
hear someone or you
hear someone telling

00:20:41.310 --> 00:20:44.490 align:middle line:90%
of her deep personal experience.

00:20:44.490 --> 00:20:46.260 align:middle line:10%
And it touches you
because you know

00:20:46.260 --> 00:20:48.000 align:middle line:10%
you've had the same experience.

00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:51.600 align:middle line:10%
There's a way that I think
that women as a gender

00:20:51.600 --> 00:20:59.280 align:middle line:10%
seem to have more ability to
have inter-permeating psyches.

00:20:59.280 --> 00:21:02.520 align:middle line:10%
I truly have this
sense that it's so.

00:21:02.520 --> 00:21:04.980 align:middle line:10%
And so if women are
in a circle and are

00:21:04.980 --> 00:21:07.410 align:middle line:10%
talking about their
own experiences,

00:21:07.410 --> 00:21:09.060 align:middle line:10%
they're talking
about themselves.

00:21:09.060 --> 00:21:12.290 align:middle line:84%
But invariably, this
sets up a resonance

00:21:12.290 --> 00:21:15.120 align:middle line:84%
in the other women who are
hearing or opening them

00:21:15.120 --> 00:21:17.890 align:middle line:84%
to the possibility
of that space.

00:21:17.890 --> 00:21:19.740 align:middle line:90%
Now, this is like taking--

00:21:19.740 --> 00:21:21.730 align:middle line:84%
all the archetypes
are in all of us.

00:21:21.730 --> 00:21:26.160 align:middle line:84%
And if we are in a
circle where they

00:21:26.160 --> 00:21:28.320 align:middle line:90%
are being spoken of deeply--

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:32.060 align:middle line:84%
not from the head, but from
living, having lived there--

00:21:32.060 --> 00:21:34.830 align:middle line:84%
that it stirs it
in the listener.

00:21:34.830 --> 00:21:37.350 align:middle line:84%
And there's something
about that experience

00:21:37.350 --> 00:21:39.570 align:middle line:90%
that women seem to do.

00:21:39.570 --> 00:21:44.550 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm also under the impression
that this is true of many

00:21:44.550 --> 00:21:48.540 align:middle line:84%
groups of people who have
become repressed, suppressed,

00:21:48.540 --> 00:21:52.260 align:middle line:84%
alienated from mainstream,
conventional, white, male,

00:21:52.260 --> 00:21:57.900 align:middle line:84%
patriarchal society, that
Latinos and Blacks and other

00:21:57.900 --> 00:22:01.470 align:middle line:84%
cultures have that same
quality and the same openness

00:22:01.470 --> 00:22:04.320 align:middle line:90%
to psychic depths.

00:22:04.320 --> 00:22:09.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the non-hierarchical,
top of the heap--

00:22:09.250 --> 00:22:11.700 align:middle line:84%
the people that are not at
the top of the heap, people

00:22:11.700 --> 00:22:14.447 align:middle line:84%
of color, indigenous
people, for one thing,

00:22:14.447 --> 00:22:15.780 align:middle line:90%
they're typically more embodied.

00:22:15.780 --> 00:22:18.906 align:middle line:90%


00:22:18.906 --> 00:22:20.550 align:middle line:84%
But it's changing
in our culture.

00:22:20.550 --> 00:22:25.120 align:middle line:84%
Our younger generation
listens to music and dances.

00:22:25.120 --> 00:22:29.730 align:middle line:84%
And there's something about
the ecstatic experience that

00:22:29.730 --> 00:22:33.900 align:middle line:84%
informs you about
a dimension that

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:37.980 align:middle line:84%
is in this realm that could be
called goddess spirituality.

00:22:37.980 --> 00:22:42.060 align:middle line:84%
And it isn't-- because the realm
of goddess spirituality is not

00:22:42.060 --> 00:22:47.280 align:middle line:84%
just the realm that women have,
because women experience god,

00:22:47.280 --> 00:22:48.780 align:middle line:90%
and women experience goddess.

00:22:48.780 --> 00:22:52.000 align:middle line:84%
And men experience god
and goddess as well.

00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:55.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Jean, I think we'll
end on that note.

00:22:55.200 --> 00:22:58.950 align:middle line:84%
It's been such a pleasure
and a heartfelt experience

00:22:58.950 --> 00:23:00.700 align:middle line:84%
for me to share
this time with you.

00:23:00.700 --> 00:23:01.510 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:23:01.510 --> 00:23:02.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:23:02.310 --> 00:23:03.780 align:middle line:90%
Time went so fast.

00:23:03.780 --> 00:23:06.810 align:middle line:84%
>> And thank you
for being with us.

